# Cookie Jar - Monorepo Standards

## Greenpill Dev Guild Principles
- Open source, transparent, regen-positive development
- Work in public with clear documentation
- Mobile-first PWA approach
- Web3-native with ethical considerations

## Monorepo Structure
- **bun workspaces** for package management
- **Conventional commits**: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `test:`
- **Quality gates**: All PRs require passing build, test, lint, type-check
- **Coverage requirements**: Never decrease below current levels (90%+ for new code)

## Development Commands

```bash
# Full stack development
bun dev                 # Local with fresh Anvil chain

# Testing & quality
bun run test            # All tests across packages (IMPORTANT: use `bun run test`, not `bun test`)
bun run test:client:coverage  # Client coverage report
bun run test:contracts:coverage  # Contract coverage report
bun lint                # Lint all packages
bun type-check          # Fast TypeScript validation (preferred)
bun build               # Build all packages
```

## Tech Stack Standards
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 + React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- **Web3**: viem + wagmi (NEVER ethers.js)  
- **Contracts**: Foundry + Solidity ^0.8.0 + OpenZeppelin
- **Testing**: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (e2e) + Foundry (contracts)
- **Protocols**: Use official SDKs (POAP, Unlock, Hypercerts, Hats)

## Quality Requirements
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode, no `any` types, exhaustive enums
- **Test coverage**: 90%+ for new code, unit + integration tests
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
- **Performance**: Core Web Vitals targets met
- **Security**: Testnet-first, explicit mainnet acknowledgment required
- **Logging**: Use `log` from `@/lib/app/logger`, never `console.log/error/warn`

## Environment & Security
- Use `.env.local` for local development
- Never commit secrets or private keys
- Default to testnets (Base Sepolia, Celo Alfajores)
- Require `// I ACKNOWLEDGE MAINNET` comment for mainnet operations
- Use Foundry keystore for production deployments

## Code Style
- **Files**: kebab-case (`cookie-jar-factory.ts`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (`CookieJarCard.tsx`)  
- **Functions**: camelCase (`getUserJars()`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_WITHDRAWAL_AMOUNT`)
- **Contracts**: PascalCase (`CookieJarFactory.sol`)

## Linting & Code Quality (Pre-Build Enforcement)

### Critical Rules (Build-Blocking Errors)
- **no-unused-vars**: Remove unused variables or prefix with `_`
- **no-console**: Use `log` from `@/lib/app/logger` instead
- **react/no-unescaped-entities**: Escape quotes (`don't` → `don&apos;t`)
- **@next/next/no-img-element**: Use `<Image />` from `next/image`
- **react-hooks/exhaustive-deps**: Include all hook dependencies

### Pre-Commit Requirements
```bash
bun type-check   # Must pass (no TypeScript errors)
bun lint         # Must pass (no ESLint errors)
bun build        # Must complete successfully
```

### Common Patterns
```typescript
// Unused variables: prefix with _
const { data, _unused } = props;

// Logging: use structured logger
import { log } from '@/lib/app/logger';
log.info('Action completed', { userId, result });

// Images: use Next.js Image component
import Image from 'next/image';
<Image src={url} alt="..." width={100} height={100} />

// JSX quotes: escape with HTML entities
<p>Don&apos;t forget to escape apostrophes</p>
<li>Use &quot;quotes&quot; for nested text</li>
```